        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> So we've all read the few threads moaning about what we are/are not getting in PoP even though it's only just hit test.</P><P>Could I suggest then that we compile a list of what we *would* like to see for Necro's in PoP?  And send that list to Verant?  Granted, it may not get implemented, it may not get seen by those who matter - but rather than just bitch, why dont we do something?</P><P>I would suggest everyone lists here what they would like to see happen, and the top 10/20 are compiled together and sent off.</P><P>Maybe include a list of all those Necro's who have gone together in compiling this list?</P><P>What would I like to see?</P><P>1) Spells that make others think 'necro lfg - grab him/her!' - currently, those people i know are more than eager to group with me, otherwise its soloing only most of the time - if VI want people to group - make people want to group with us<BR>2) Spells more readily available - no spell should only drop off one level 60 mob - there should be other routes that those not in the top guilds can take to get these spells.<BR>3) Those spells that are off lower level that are insanely rare (group dmf, demi lich etc) available via other routes.<BR>4) Give our spells a chance to actually land of boss mobs - so we aren't constantly seeing resist, resist, resist (this makes not only necros but casters rather pointless on some mobs)<BR>5) A better pure tanking pet that can be quested for - this spell being not a dropped spell <BR>6) You know full well that PoP is going to have gear in it that is going to make the epic look like 'a rusty scythe' - so why not up the drop rates on the eye/slimeblood and cloak components?  I am not saying that they should be common drops, but they are insanely rare at the moment.  I personally think everyone should have a <font color="red">chance</font> to get thier epic, even if they are not in a large/uber guild.</P><P>There is probably more, but what would others like to see?</P><P>Tinantier DeSepulkra<BR>56 Defiler of the Silent Minority<BR>Terris-Thule</font></td>

